pgTitle: Aeroflot accidents and incidents in the 1980s

rows.text: Both the fuselage and the wings sustained damage by the wheel studs when the aircraft performed a hard landing on its skis.
Destroyed by a fire that broke out on the flight deck.
Landed on soft terrain and sank, breaking off the engine.
Crashed into a hill near Gelendzhik under unspecified circumstances.
Sank when the frozen lake it was standing on broke.
Overturned on landing on a river bank, coming to rest upside down in the river.
Overran the runway, hitting an obstacle.
Destroyed by fire in a maintenance facility at Minsk-1 Airport.
Crashed while performing a crop spraying mission.
Crashed near Kostroma while en route a domestic scheduled passenger service.
Could not gain altitude after takeoff, lost speed, and crash-landed. The aircraft had ten illegal passengers on board.
Lost speed and crashed in the Stavropol Krai after the pilot tried to gain altitude and the aircraft banked steeply. Was performing a crop spraying mission.
Sank when the ice surface it was being towed over for repairs cracked.

Crashed kilometres (mi) southwest of Syktyvkar after it hit trees when attempting a forced landing due to a fire in the cargo hold. The aircraft was due to operate a domestic scheduled Syktyvkar–Moscow passenger service.
One of the wings struck trees when the pilot was maneuvering the aircraft to drop off mail.
Struck a -metre (ft) high mountain, kilometres (mi) away from Alma-Ata, soon after it departed from Alma-Ata Airport for a cargo service.
Sank when the ice of a frozen lake the aircraft had landed on broke.
Involved in a ground accident alongside two other aircraft.
Main undercarriage broke off upon landing.
Lost power on takeoff and force-landed in a ravine.
Crashed and caught fire, kilometres (mi) away from Tobolsk, after it struck the top of a chimney.
Struck the ground after the pilot unintentionally moved the steering wheel.
Lost control when it entered a turbulence region at low altitude.
Crash-landed minutes after takeoff following fuel exhaustion.
Struck a -metre (ft) high mountain, kilometres (mi) east of Aiykam.
Crashed when it struck the ground on approach to Kodinsk, inbound from Krasnoyarsk on a domestic scheduled passenger service.
Overran the runway on landing and hit a concrete mast.
